Employment and Labour minister Thulas Nxesi has gazetted the new sectoral determinations for workers in South Africa’s wholesale and retail sectors. The changes take effect from 1 March 2022 alongside recent changes to South Africa’s minimum wage. These wages establish the minimum baseline across the sector and workers can earn significantly more based on their position and the company that they work for. Workers are also paid in accordance with what part of South Africa they are based in. The below table shows the monthly wages for workers in both Area A and Area B: